body_html:
The message "nnapi error: unable to open library libneuralnetworks.so" is ok if the device isn't running a recent version of android. That message has also been removed from TF Lite recently.

As for the null pointer:

  • make sure you called AllocatedTensors
  • make sure the data type (uint8) is appropriate for your model.
